The House Committee on Rules offers the following substitute to HB 677:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 1 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 general provisions of health, so as to provide for certain placement procedures for children
3 upon discharge from a hospital or psychiatric residential treatment facility in certain
4 circumstances; to provide for related matters; to provide for applicability; to repeal
5 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 1 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
9 provisions of health, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
10 "31-1-26.
11 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
12 (1) 'Acute psychiatric care' means a level of care that is highly structured for patients
13 who are a risk to themselves or others.
14 (2) 'Health benefit policy' means any individual or group plan, policy, or contract for
15 major medical, hospitalization, or other healthcare services issued, delivered, issued for
16 delivery, or renewed in this state by a healthcare corporation, health maintenance
- 1 -

